product_name: CliniqueMoisture Surge 100H Auto-Replenishing Hydrator Gel Moisturizer with Hyaluronic Acid
summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingClinique Moisture Surge 100H Auto-Replenishing Hydrator is a refreshing oil-free face moisturizer with aloe bioferment and hyaluronic acid.
details: DetailsBenefitsAll Skin Types.Concern: Dehydration, dry skin.Delivers instant hydration that soothes in 3 seconds.100% instantly show a boost in hydration and glow.Many things can dehydrate your skin, including stress, lack of sleep, pollution, air travel, and time spent in the sun. Fight back with Moisture Surge™ 100H Hydrator. Clinique’s gel moisturizer penetrates deep into skin’s surface for 100 hours of stabilizing hydration.An antioxidant blend of vitamins C and E helps protect against daily dehydrators so your skin is more resilient.Skin feels soothed with hydration in 3 seconds, and it keeps on glowing.Preps for Makeup: Lightweight, refreshing moisturizer with hyaluronic acid provides a smooth canvas for makeup application.Free Of: Fragrance, Parabens, Phthalates, Oil, Drying alcohol.Dermatologist tested. Safe for sensitive skin. Allergy tested. 100% fragrance free.Key IngredientsAloe bioferment: The aloe vera plant is concentrated over 500 times, then further transformed into a bioferment through a meticulous 10-step fermentation process over 5+ days. The result is a nutrient-rich ingredient that helps skin retain moisture.Hyaluronic acid: This moisture-binding ingredient helps create a “moisture reservoir” for ideal hydration. Clinique’s formula is expertly blended with two different molecular weights of hyaluronic acid.Blend of vitamins C and E: Helps provide antioxidant protection against daily dehydrators.Auto-Replenishing Technology: Using activated aloe water and caffeine, it helps trigger skin’s own rehydration system.Research ResultsAfter one use:100% show a boost in hydration* and glow.**Boosts moisture immediately by +174%.Provides 100 hours of stabilizing hydration.*Clinical testing on 19 women.**Clinical testing on 27 women.After one week:99% say skin feels deeply hydrated.*95% say skin looks plump.*91% say skin looks glowing.*98% say skin feels more resilient.*95% say skin feels healthier.**Consumer testing on 110 women.Item 2576602How To UseUse moisturizer morning and night on clean skin. Can be used under or over makeup and also as a 5-minute moisture mask.IngredientsWater\Aqua\Eau, Dimethicone, Butylene Glycol, Glycerin, Trisiloxane, Trehalose, Sucrose, Ammonium Acryloyldimethyltaurate/Vp Copolymer, Hydroxyethyl Urea, Camellia Sinensis (Green Tea) Leaf Extract, Silybum Marianum (Lady's Thistle) Extract, Betula Alba (Birch) Bark Extract, Saccharomyces Lysate Extract, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Water, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Extract, Thermus Thermophillus Ferment, Caffeine, Sorbitol, Palmitoyl Hexapeptide-12, Sodium Hyaluronate, Caprylyl Glycol, Oleth-10, Sodium Polyaspartate, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Polysaccharides, Lactobacillus Ferment Lysate, Saccharide Isomerate, Hydrogenated Lecithin, Tocopheryl Acetate, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Glyceryl Polymethacrylate, Tromethamine, PEG-8, Hexylene Glycol, Magnesium Ascorbyl Phosphate, Citric Acid, BHT, Disodium EDTA, Sodium Citrate, Potassium Sorbate, Sodium Benzoate, Phenoxyethanol, Red 4 (CI 14700), Yellow 5 (CI 19140).Please be aware that ingredient lists may change or vary from time to time. Please refer to the ingredient list on the product package you receive for the most up to date list of ingredients.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Great for sensitive skin
reviews.comments: I highly recommend this product. I have very sensitive skin and it works great. Also not having a scent helps to not give me a migraine.

reviews.headline: Product had silicone in it
reviews.comments: Went into store and asked for a day and night moisturizer that did not contain silicone. Young lady said this was the best. Unfortunately it does have silicone in it, returned.

reviews.headline: I will continue to purchase this product forever
reviews.comments: yes I love this product and how much it has help my face skin at the age of 66

reviews.headline: Very hydrating gel
reviews.comments: This is my second order of this moisturizer and I love it . I use it in the morning and at night. It makes my face feel smooth and clean. I can see and feel the difference in my skin .

reviews.headline: Great moisturizer
reviews.comments: This is the only moisturizer I use and it works for me.   I love it and it helps keep my face fresh and glowing.

reviews.headline: I love the Moisture Surge!
reviews.comments: I have been buying this product for 2 years. I absolutely love it! I can feel a huge difference in my skin when I forget to use it in the morning. My skin is much softer, not dry, clear, no complaints at all.

reviews.headline: Tried and True
reviews.comments: On my 5th tub! Have tried many other brands, but nothing compares to this hydrating, light weight formula.

reviews.headline: Buyer beware
reviews.comments: While I tried the other moisture surge without aloe, I didnt have any reaction but a week after using this specific one, I started to have red, raw and itchy, dry flaky and scaly patches on my skin. Now about $200 and a dermatologist later, I found out this product gave me eczema on my eyes, cheek and jawline. I don't have a history of eczema in my family or myself and don't have sensitive skin so this reaction was a tough one. Not saying it won't work for everyone, judging by the reviews many people have success with it because everyones skin is different but just be super aware of your skin as it can take awhile for a rash to show up.

reviews.headline: 100% useless. Bring back the old formula.
reviews.comments:
This stuff was so bad, it would take me five minutes to list all the cons. The two main issues are that it completely dries out Skin, it's almost like you didn't even put any of it on. Even worse than that, my skin became very red, hot to the touch and irritated.
The old formula didn't have any cons at all. I don't know what they've done to this but the 100 H is awful.

reviews.headline: Best cream
reviews.comments: This is one of the best moisturizer it keeps my skin soft and moist the whole day.

reviews.headline: Allergic reaction
reviews.comments: I really wanted to love this, but I developed a bad reaction after a week of use. I experienced break outs and itchiness, likely from the "lady's thistle" ingredient with is related to ragweed. Allergy-prone gals beware.

reviews.headline: Wonderful Moisturizer
reviews.comments: I hadn't used this product for many years, always wanting to try what's new and maybe better??  This moisturizer is truly the best for any skin type!  It goes on so lightly easily blends into my skin and has a coolness which helps my rosacea!  I highly recommend this product!

reviews.headline: I definitely will buy again
reviews.comments: Keeps my skin so wrinkle free

reviews.headline: Great moisturizer!
reviews.comments: I like to use this at night in between my retinol and lactic acid treatments as it is really soothing to my skin after being irritated by them. My skin feels hydrated and soft in the morning.

reviews.headline: Awesome product
reviews.comments: This product is so lightweight once u put it on. Love it!

reviews.headline: Best Moisturizer
reviews.comments: Keeps my aging skin clear of dry spots and acne.  Also improves appearance of fine lines around my eyes.  I believe it is the best moisturizer!
reviews.nickname: Please do no include my personal informa

reviews.headline: Excellent
reviews.comments: I have normal to dry skin, this is a wonderful hylaronic acid gel cream.  I was afraid it would be too heavy, but it sinks right in, left non greasy feel, wears well under makeup and as the norm for Clinique, no fragrance, which is a huge benefit.

reviews.headline: Best thing ever
reviews.comments: I got this in November with my birthday gift and just ran out but I will be repurchasing. This is the best moisturizer I have ever used

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: I would definitely recommend this for literally anybody

reviews.headline: Gave me whiteheads
reviews.comments: I have been using this product for a year now and I've gone through 3-4 jars since my first purchase. It helped with hydrating and moisturizing, but I was dealing with little tiny white heads and red bumps allll over my face for a year. I had no idea where they were coming from!! After a year of trying to figure it out, I stopped using this product and immediately saw my skin get better... This gel was clogging my pores and I had no idea. I was a loyal customer but now I will never buy this product again.

faceoff_positive.comments: I absolutely LOVE this product!!! I have been using Clinique beauty and skincare products for over fifteen years!!! I was a regular user of their Moisture Surge 72 Hour Auto-Replenishing Hydrator product until I heard about their exciting latest development of their Moisture Surge 100 Hour Auto-Replenishing Hydrator!! I thought I was impressed at 72 hours, but this new product, not only stays on and works longer - which don't get me wrong, is a huge win, but it also feels softer and lighter on my skin - definitely the added extra secret ingredient - aloe vera!! I love how gentle this moisturizer feels going on. It is super soft, light, and airy!! My skin still feels breathable after applying, not heavy and weighted down like some other brand moisturizers have made me feel in the past. Most importantly, this moisturizer is pure, clean, and genuine - NOT full of harsh chemicals!! This is HIGE for me!!! I am currently going through aggressive acne treatments, including a retinol rx, (under a dermatologist's care, of course!!) and it is extremely hard to find a moisturizer that is truly soothing and appropriate for my newly sensitive skin as anything with perfume or nasty chemicals causes my face to immediately start burning, turn red, and even peel off!! Thankfully, Clinique's Moisture Surge 100 Hour Auto-Replenishing Hydrator came to the rescue!!! This product has truly helped in my skincare recovery journey and will continue to be my daily go-to product!!! It has made my skin softer, smoother, and healthier!! I feel refreshed and rejuvenated after applying a thin layer - as a little goes a long way. Many days (especially with the pandemic) I feel confident enough to just wear this moisturizer out of the house (sans makeup). My skin looks silky, hydrated, and refreshed!! I've already had a few friends mention that my I look more relaxed, like I just got back from vacation lol!! So, it definitely seems this product is not only working for me, but it feels good, and it looks good on me!!! I would absolutely recommend this wonderful product, Clinique's Moisture Surge 100 Hour Auto-Replenishing Hydrator to anyone interested in a long lasting, lightweight, dewy, gel moisturizer that is full of hydration, safe for sensitive skin, suitable for all skin types, and does NOT contain perfume, fragrance, parabens, or phthalates!!
faceoff_positive.headline: My Skin Feels Soft, Silky, Hydrated, Refreshed, & Healthy!!!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I loooooove this face cream for my sensitive skin as a part of my routine. It works descent even as a standalone product for me and I can see noticeable difference between when I am using it and when I go without. I have had ZERO breakouts with it so far which is saying a lot.

What I absolutely HATE and DESPISE about this product is the container. Not only is Clinique totally on the hook for budget cutting corners with an open-top design rather than a closed air-tight pump for similarly priced products and brands, but the container and its lid are as slippery as black ice frozen over a slip-n-slide with some olive oil added on top for bad measure. I am NOT exaggerating when I say that it is physically difficult to NOT let this container slip out of your hands or off of a table-top surface. It would seem some sadistic person at Clinique literally designed this product to spill to pad thier profit margins. I have thus far lost about 50% of my jar to the floor, the table, and my friend's dress and have actually applied about 2% of it to my face. I am not kidding when I say that they somehow managed to create a finish on this thing that is the likely one of the slipperiest substances known to mankind. I tried to contact the company about this but their message button on the support page is broken.
faceoff_negative.headline: Amazing product but worst packaging in cosmetics history
